Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Blend sugar and cinnamon together. Brush both sides of bread lightly with margarine. Generously sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture. Cut into 1-inch cubes. BAKE cubes on a baking sheet with a lip for 8-9 minutes, or until golden brown, stirring once. Set aside to cool. Toss together croutons and berries. Spread evenly into an 8x8x2-inch pan. Spread whipped topping evenly to cover filling*. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar, if desired.